01:23:04,106 --> 01:23:05,315
- Thanks.
- You too, Henry.

1341
01:23:05,649 --> 01:23:07,151
[DOOR BUZZES]

1342
01:23:08,193 --> 01:23:10,070
[CHATTERING]

1343
01:23:14,116 --> 01:23:15,159
MAN:
Mrs. Hill, come here.

1344
01:23:15,325 --> 01:23:16,493
Come on.

1345
01:23:19,872 --> 01:23:21,915
You girls stay right here.

1346
01:23:22,332 --> 01:23:25,586
- I want you to hold hands.
- Okay, go right up to the front.

1347
01:23:25,919 --> 01:23:27,838
- Let's go.
- GUARD: How you doing?

1348
01:23:28,005 --> 01:23:30,215
KAREN: Good, how are you?
GUARD: Very well, thank you.

1349
01:23:42,477 --> 01:23:44,938
- What you talking about?
- I saw her name in the register.

1350
01:23:45,105 --> 01:23:47,274
HENRY: Jesus Christ.
KAREN: You want her to visit you?

1351
01:23:47,441 --> 01:23:51,111
Let her stay up all night crying
and writing letters to the parole board.

1352
01:23:51,278 --> 01:23:54,448
What am I doing here?
Where am I? I'm in jail.

1353
01:23:54,615 --> 01:23:56,742
I can't stop people
from coming to see me.

1354
01:23:56,909 --> 01:24:00,287
Good, let her sneak this stuff in
for you every week.

1355
01:24:00,454 --> 01:24:04,082
- Let her fight these bastards every week!
- Look what you're doing! Stop it!

1356
01:24:04,249 --> 01:24:05,667
[BABY CRYING]

1357
01:24:05,834 --> 01:24:07,794
- Shh.
- KAREN: I'm sorry.

1358
01:24:08,295 --> 01:24:10,756
Let her sneak this shit in for you.

1359
01:24:11,798 --> 01:24:13,634
Will you stop it, Karen?

1360
01:24:14,092 --> 01:24:16,637
- Let her do it!
- Stop it!

1361
01:24:24,811 --> 01:24:28,106
KAREN:
Nobody's helping me. I'm all alone.

1362
01:24:29,149 --> 01:24:31,151
Belle and Morrie are broke.

1363
01:24:31,568 --> 01:24:34,780
I asked your friend Remo
for the money that he owes you.

1364
01:24:34,947 --> 01:24:36,323
You know what he told me?

1365
01:24:36,490 --> 01:24:40,077
He told me to take my kids down
to the police station and get on welfare.

1366
01:24:40,244 --> 01:24:42,204
It's gonna be okay.

1367
01:24:42,412 --> 01:24:46,500
Even Paulie, since he got out, I've never
seen him. I never see anybody anymore.

1368
01:24:46,667 --> 01:24:49,461
It's only you and me.
That's what happens when you go away.

1369
01:24:49,628 --> 01:24:53,632
I told you that we're on our own.
Forget everybody else. Forget Paulie.

1370
01:24:54,633 --> 01:24:58,637
As long as he's on parole,
he doesn't want anybody doing anything.

1371
01:25:01,098 --> 01:25:03,350
- I can't do it.
- Yes, you can. Listen to me.

1372
01:25:03,517 --> 01:25:06,103
All I need for you
is to keep bringing me the stuff.

1373
01:25:06,270 --> 01:25:08,855
I got a guy in here from Pittsburgh
who'll help me move it.

1374
01:25:09,022 --> 01:25:10,649
In a month we're gonna be fine.

1375
01:25:10,816 --> 01:25:13,151
- We won't need anybody.
- I'm afraid.

1376
01:25:13,318 --> 01:25:15,237
I'm afraid if Paulie finds out....

1377
01:25:15,404 --> 01:25:16,822
Don't worry about him.

1378
01:25:16,989 --> 01:25:20,534
He is not helping us out.
Is he putting any food on the table?

1379
01:25:21,702 --> 01:25:23,161
We've gotta help each other.

1380
01:25:23,328 --> 01:25:26,999
We've just gotta be really careful
while we do it.

1381
01:25:31,670 --> 01:25:33,880
I don't want to hear a word
about her anymore.

1382
01:25:34,047 --> 01:25:35,090
Never.

1383
01:26:00,657 --> 01:26:02,117
GIRLS:
Daddy!

1384
01:26:03,744 --> 01:26:05,996
JUDY: We missed you.
RUTH: Are you here to stay?

1385
01:26:06,163 --> 01:26:09,750
JUDY: Did you see our pictures?
I did the one with the house and rainbow.

1386
01:26:09,916 --> 01:26:11,335
RUTH:
I did the sun.

1387
01:26:11,501 --> 01:26:15,422
JUDY: My chorus concert is in two weeks.
Are you coming?

1388
01:26:16,256 --> 01:26:18,091
Do you like the house?

1389
01:26:19,384 --> 01:26:21,261
Karen, get packed.
We're moving out of here.

1390
01:26:21,428 --> 01:26:22,637
With what?

1391
01:26:22,846 --> 01:26:25,932
Don't worry, with what.
Just start looking for a new house.

1392
01:26:26,099 --> 01:26:29,519
I got to go to Pittsburgh in the morning.
Those guys there owe me $15,000.

1393
01:26:29,686 --> 01:26:31,605
We'll be all right. I got things lined up.

1394
01:26:31,772 --> 01:26:34,441
Pittsburgh? You have to go see
your parole officer tomorrow.

1395
01:26:34,608 --> 01:26:37,527
Don't worry about it.
Everything's gonna be fine.

1396
01:26:38,236 --> 01:26:40,364
- Who wants to go to Uncle Paulie's?
- BOTH: Me!

1397
01:26:43,533 --> 01:26:45,786
[CHATTERING]

1398
01:26:50,916 --> 01:26:52,501
What do you want?

1399
01:26:52,751 --> 01:26:54,795
WOMAN:
Sweetheart, let Mommy eat.

1400
01:26:58,256 --> 01:27:01,134
You look good.
Did you eat this good in the joint?

1401
01:27:03,261 --> 01:27:05,097
I don't want any more of that shit.

1402
01:27:05,263 --> 01:27:06,306
What shit?

1403
01:27:06,473 --> 01:27:09,101
- Just stay away from the garbage.
- Look, Paulie--

1404
01:27:09,267 --> 01:27:12,437
I'm not talking about what you did inside.
You did what you had to do.

1405
01:27:12,604 --> 01:27:14,898
I'm talking about now. From now.
Here and now.

1406
01:27:16,191 --> 01:27:18,944
- Why would I get into that?
- Don't make a jerk out of me.

1407
01:27:19,111 --> 01:27:20,654
Just don't do it.

1408
01:27:24,408 --> 01:27:27,369
I want to talk to you about Jimmy.
You gotta watch out for him.

1409
01:27:27,536 --> 01:27:30,497
He's a good earner, but he's wild,
takes too many chances.

1410
01:27:30,664 --> 01:27:32,833
I know Jimmy. You think
I would take chances like him?

1411
01:27:32,999 --> 01:27:34,793
Tommy's a good kid, but he's crazy.

1412
01:27:34,960 --> 01:27:36,600
He's a cowboy.
He's got too much to prove.

1413
01:27:36,753 --> 01:27:38,547
You gotta watch out for kids like this.

1414
01:27:38,713 --> 01:27:41,341
I know what they are.
I only use them for certain things.

1415
01:27:41,508 --> 01:27:44,010
I ain't gonna get fucked like Gribbs,
you understand?

1416
01:27:44,177 --> 01:27:48,515
Gribbs is 70 years old. The fucking guy's
gonna die in prison. I don't need that.

1417
01:27:48,849 --> 01:27:52,727
So I'm warning everybody. Everybody.
Could be my son, could be anybody.

1418
01:27:53,270 --> 01:27:55,814
Gribbs got 20 years just
for saying hello to some fuck...

1419
01:27:55,981 --> 01:27:58,066
who was sneaking behind his back,
selling junk.

1420
01:27:58,233 --> 01:28:00,694
I don't need that.
That won't happen to me, understand?

1421
01:28:00,861 --> 01:28:03,113
You know you're out early
because I got you a job.

1422
01:28:03,280 --> 01:28:05,157
I don't need this heat,
you understand that?

1423
01:28:05,323 --> 01:28:09,035
You see anybody fucking around
with this shit you're gonna tell me, right?

1424
01:28:09,202 --> 01:28:10,245
That means anybody.

1425
01:28:10,412 --> 01:28:11,455
- All right.
- Yeah?

1426
01:28:11,621 --> 01:28:13,331
Yeah. Of course.

1427
01:28:20,922 --> 01:28:22,883
HENRY: <i>Took me about a week
of sneaking around...</i>

1428
01:28:23,049 --> 01:28:24,885
<i>before I could unload
the Pittsburgh stuff.</i>

1429
01:28:25,051 --> 01:28:27,512
<i>But when I did, it was a real score.</i>

1430
01:28:27,679 --> 01:28:30,223
<i>I started using Sandy's place
to mix the stuff.</i>

1431
01:28:30,390 --> 01:28:32,809
<i>And even with Sandy snorting
more than she mixed...</i>

1432
01:28:32,976 --> 01:28:35,604
<i>I could see that
this was a really good business.</i>

1433
01:28:35,770 --> 01:28:38,190
<i>I made $12,000 in my second week.</i>

1434
01:28:38,773 --> 01:28:41,860
<i>I had a down payment on my house
and things were really rolling.</i>

1435
01:28:42,027 --> 01:28:46,239
<i>All I had to do was every once in a while
tell Sandy that I loved her.</i>

1436
01:28:49,868 --> 01:28:51,912
<i>But it was perfect, I'm telling you.</i>

1437
01:28:52,078 --> 01:28:54,456
<i>As long as I kept getting
the stuff from Pittsburgh...</i>

1438
01:28:54,623 --> 01:28:56,333
<i>I knew Paulie would never find out.</i>

1439
01:28:56,500 --> 01:29:00,378
<i>Within a couple of weeks,
it got so big I needed some help.</i>

1440
01:29:00,754 --> 01:29:03,548
<i>So I got Jimmy and Tommy
to come in with me.</i>

1441
01:29:03,924 --> 01:29:05,467
It's fucking great.

1442
01:29:05,800 --> 01:29:06,927
Mr. Conway.

1443
01:29:12,766 --> 01:29:14,684
- Bring your pay slips?
- Yeah.

1444
01:29:17,771 --> 01:29:20,106
KAREN:
Four and a half months of dirt.

1445
01:29:20,690 --> 01:29:23,235
- It's so good.
- KAREN: I did it.

1446
01:29:24,402 --> 01:29:26,988
- Do you love it?
- BELLE: It's wonderful.

1447
01:29:27,447 --> 01:29:31,201
KAREN: And this we just had to have
made special. Go ahead, sit in it, Belle.

1448
01:29:31,368 --> 01:29:33,912
The others you couldn't even sit in.

1449
01:29:34,120 --> 01:29:35,622
Okay, you ready?

1450
01:29:35,789 --> 01:29:37,958
Watch the wall with the rock.

1451
01:29:42,003 --> 01:29:44,005
[KAREN AND BELLE LAUGHING]

1452
01:29:45,590 --> 01:29:48,385
The electricians did it special. Come on.

1453
01:29:49,553 --> 01:29:51,304
Come on. All right.

1454
01:29:51,471 --> 01:29:55,100
This was imported. It came in two pieces.
Do you believe what they can do?

1455
01:29:55,267 --> 01:29:56,601
HENRY:
It's nice, huh?

1456
01:29:56,768 --> 01:29:58,770
Henry, come over here.
Did you and Jimmy talk?

1457
01:29:58,937 --> 01:30:01,273
I talked to him,
and he's looking into everything.

1458
01:30:01,439 --> 01:30:04,818
This'll make the Air France haul
look like goddamn peanuts.

1459
01:30:04,985 --> 01:30:07,237
- Shh! Come on.
- He's gonna do it, right?

1460
01:30:07,404 --> 01:30:09,155
I told you. He'll check everything out.

1461
01:30:09,322 --> 01:30:11,992
He's looking into it.
We'll see what happens. No promises.

1462
01:30:12,158 --> 01:30:16,329
I know. Do you understand?
There's millions in there. And I've been...

1463
01:30:16,496 --> 01:30:20,125
bleeding for this caper, been cultivating
this son of a bitch for two years.

1464
01:30:20,333 --> 01:30:23,378
He owes me $20,000. Once in a lifetime.
I could retire.

1465
01:30:23,545 --> 01:30:27,424
No more nut every week.
No more bullshit. My dream comes true.

1466
01:30:27,591 --> 01:30:29,634
Morrie, let's get a drink.

1467
01:30:29,968 --> 01:30:33,096
HARRY: <i>These are the guys that Jimmy
put together for what turned out to be...</i>

1468
01:30:33,263 --> 01:30:37,142
<i>the biggest heist in American history:
the Lufthansa heist.</i>

1469
01:30:38,393 --> 01:30:41,104
<i>Tommy and Carbone were gonna grab
the outside guard...</i>

1470
01:30:41,271 --> 01:30:43,773
<i>and make him get us in the front door.</i>

1471
01:30:45,025 --> 01:30:48,320
<i>Frenchy and Joe Buddha
had to round up the workers.</i>

1472
01:30:48,862 --> 01:30:52,866
<i>Johnny Roastbeef had to keep them
all tied up and away from the alarms.</i>

1473
01:30:53,658 --> 01:30:55,869
<i>Even Stacks Edwards got in on it.</i>

1474
01:30:56,036 --> 01:30:59,539
<i>He used to hang around the lounge
and play guitar. Everybody loved Stacks.</i>

1475
01:30:59,706 --> 01:31:02,167
<i>What he was supposed to do
was steal the panel truck...</i>

1476
01:31:02,334 --> 01:31:05,462
<i>and afterwards compact it
by a friend of ours out in Jersey.</i>

1477
01:31:05,629 --> 01:31:08,006
<i>Only Morrie was driving us nuts.</i>

1478
01:31:08,173 --> 01:31:10,175
Morrie, have a drink and shut up.

1479
01:31:10,342 --> 01:31:13,386
HENRY: <i>Just because he set this up,
he felt he could bust Jimmy's balls...</i>

1480
01:31:13,553 --> 01:31:16,097
<i>for an advance on the money
we were going to steal.</i>

1481
01:31:16,264 --> 01:31:19,893
<i>He didn't mean anything by it.
That's just the way he was.</i>

1482
01:31:26,775 --> 01:31:30,904
<i>I had everybody working for me.
Even our old baby-sitter, Lois Byrd.</i>

1483
01:31:33,823 --> 01:31:35,241
Did you have a good flight?

1484
01:31:35,408 --> 01:31:37,911
I hate Pittsburgh.
Where did you find such creeps?

1485
01:31:38,119 --> 01:31:40,038
Come on, they're not that bad.

1486
01:31:41,247 --> 01:31:43,124
And it's worth it, isn't it?

1487
01:31:43,416 --> 01:31:45,877
Is this the same baby you used last week?

1488
01:31:46,044 --> 01:31:49,130
No, that one was my sister's.
This is Deirdra's.

1489
01:31:50,006 --> 01:31:51,049
Big yawn.

1490
01:31:51,216 --> 01:31:53,051
KAREN:
She looks just like you.

1491
01:31:53,843 --> 01:31:56,179
That's what the stewardess said.

1492
01:31:56,971 --> 01:31:59,099
[KAREN AND LOIS
COOING AND LAUGHING]

1493
01:32:08,817 --> 01:32:10,777
Take it easy, Sandy.

1494
01:32:10,944 --> 01:32:13,655
Come on, give me a break.
You got enough here to go around.

1495
01:32:13,822 --> 01:32:17,158
You got all day. Just make it last,
all right? Take it easy.

1496
01:32:17,617 --> 01:32:19,452
- I got to go.
- Where are you going?

1497
01:32:19,619 --> 01:32:23,707
Don't start. You know I gotta go
do this thing. Fuck, where are my keys?

1498
01:32:24,999 --> 01:32:26,376
Over there.

1499
01:32:26,543 --> 01:32:28,253
It's a mess. It's like a pig pen.

1500
01:32:28,420 --> 01:32:30,463
What do you think
I got you the dishwasher for?

1501
01:32:30,630 --> 01:32:32,424
I hate doing the dishes. Fucks up my nails.

1502
01:32:32,590 --> 01:32:34,300
How could you hate it?
You got to be smart.

1503
01:32:34,467 --> 01:32:37,637
Look at all this powder around here.
That could put us away forever.

1504
01:32:37,804 --> 01:32:40,014
- Loosen up.
- Whoa, what are you doing?

1505
01:32:41,141 --> 01:32:44,477
- You know, I gotta....
- You don't have to go anywhere.

1506
01:32:45,645 --> 01:32:47,147
Make them wait.

1507
01:32:54,654 --> 01:32:55,947
[THEME MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO]

1508
01:32:56,114 --> 01:32:57,914
ANNOUNCER [ON RADIO]:
<i>Nobody knows for sure...</i>

1509
01:32:58,074 --> 01:33:00,201
<i>just how much was taken
in the daring pre-dawn raid...</i>

1510
01:33:00,368 --> 01:33:02,996
<i>at the Lufthansa cargo terminal
at Kennedy Airport.</i>

1511
01:33:03,163 --> 01:33:06,875
<i>The FBI says $2 million,
Port Authority Police say $4 million--</i>

1512
01:33:07,041 --> 01:33:09,961
[SCREAMING]

1513
01:33:10,128 --> 01:33:12,297
Jimmy!

1514
01:33:12,464 --> 01:33:14,299
Those sons of bitches!

1515
01:33:14,466 --> 01:33:16,801
REPORTER [ON RADIO]:
<i>...from the scene of the heist at JFK.</i>

1516
01:33:16,968 --> 01:33:20,597
<i>It looks like a big one. Maybe the biggest
this town has ever seen.</i>

1517
01:33:22,515 --> 01:33:24,684
Come here, you! Come here!

1518
01:33:25,727 --> 01:33:28,438
Look at this genius. This genius!

1519
01:33:32,859 --> 01:33:34,527
ROASTBEEF:
Merry Christmas.

1520
01:33:39,282 --> 01:33:41,701
- Hello, who's this?
- That's my wife.

1521
01:33:42,660 --> 01:33:45,955
Come here.
I want to show you something, Jimmy.

1522
01:33:48,666 --> 01:33:50,043
Isn't she gorgeous?

1523
01:33:50,210 --> 01:33:53,379
I bought it for my wife.
It's a coupe. I love that car.

1524
01:33:56,216 --> 01:33:59,052
What did I tell you?
I talked to you before, didn't I?

1525
01:33:59,219 --> 01:34:00,553
Didn't I say what was going on?

1526
01:34:00,720 --> 01:34:02,806
Didn't I say not to go buy anything
for a while?

1527
01:34:02,972 --> 01:34:05,975
- The fucking car?
- It's a wedding gift from my mother.

1528
01:34:06,142 --> 01:34:08,269
It's under her name. I just got married.

1529
01:34:08,436 --> 01:34:11,231
- I love that car.
- Excuse me, darling, for just a second.

1530
01:34:11,397 --> 01:34:13,691
- ROASTBEEF: I just got married.
- Are you nuts?

1531
01:34:13,858 --> 01:34:16,486
- What are you getting excited for?
- Are you stupid?

1532
01:34:16,653 --> 01:34:19,155
We got a million bulls out there.
Everybody's watching us.

1533
01:34:19,322 --> 01:34:21,199
And you get a fucking car. I'm excited?

1534
01:34:21,366 --> 01:34:23,409
It's under my mother's name.
It's a wedding gift.

1535
01:34:23,576 --> 01:34:25,620
I don't give a fuck. Are you stupid?

1536
01:34:25,787 --> 01:34:27,747
Didn't you hear what I said?
Don't buy anything.

1537
01:34:27,914 --> 01:34:31,626
Don't get anything. Nothing big.
What's the matter with you?

1538
01:34:32,001 --> 01:34:33,378
What are you getting excited for?

1539
01:34:33,545 --> 01:34:36,881
Because you're going to get us all
fucking pinched. What are you, stupid?

1540
01:34:37,048 --> 01:34:39,801
- What's the matter with you?
- I apologize.

1541
01:34:41,261 --> 01:34:44,472
- I'm sorry.
- What the fuck is the matter with you?

1542
01:34:46,766 --> 01:34:48,101
I'm sorry.

1543
01:34:50,603 --> 01:34:54,107
I'm sorry, Jimmy.
It's under my mother's name.

1544
01:34:54,774 --> 01:34:57,235
What'd you say? You being
a fucking wise guy with me?

1545
01:34:57,402 --> 01:35:00,530
- I'm sorry. I apologize.
- What did I tell you?

1546
01:35:00,989 --> 01:35:04,117
What did I tell you?
You don't buy anything, you hear me?

1547
01:35:04,284 --> 01:35:05,743
Don't buy anything!

1548
01:35:05,910 --> 01:35:07,495
I'm sorry, Jimmy.

1549
01:35:10,748 --> 01:35:13,167
The fat fuck, he ought to wear a sign.

1550
01:35:20,633 --> 01:35:22,969
I can't believe this.
Are you stupid or what?

1551
01:35:23,136 --> 01:35:24,470
Excuse me.

1552
01:35:24,721 --> 01:35:26,389
- What's the matter?
- Take it off.

1553
01:35:26,556 --> 01:35:29,517
- Why? What's the matter?
- Take it off!

1554
01:35:31,686 --> 01:35:35,231
Didn't I tell you not to get anything big
and not to attract attention?

1555
01:35:35,398 --> 01:35:38,484
In two days, one guy gets a Caddy
and one gets a $20,000 mink.

1556
01:35:38,651 --> 01:35:40,528
- Bring it fucking back.
- I'll bring it back.

1557
