He's a goodfella, one of us."</i>

1774
01:50:09,021 --> 01:50:10,397
<i>You understand?</i>

1775
01:50:11,064 --> 01:50:13,275
<i>We were goodfellas. Wiseguys.</i>

1776
01:50:15,861 --> 01:50:19,239
<i>But Jimmy and I could never be made
because we had Irish blood.</i>

1777
01:50:19,406 --> 01:50:21,867
<i>It didn't matter my mother was Sicilian.</i>

1778
01:50:22,117 --> 01:50:26,038
<i>To become a member of a crew,
you've got to be 100% Italian...</i>

1779
01:50:26,205 --> 01:50:29,208
<i>so they can trace your relatives
back to the old country.</i>

1780
01:50:36,548 --> 01:50:38,884
<i>It's the highest honor they can give you.</i>

1781
01:50:39,051 --> 01:50:41,553
<i>It means you belong
to a family and a crew.</i>

1782
01:50:41,929 --> 01:50:44,473
<i>It means nobody can fuck around
with you.</i>

1783
01:50:45,015 --> 01:50:47,392
<i>It also means you could
fuck around with anybody...</i>

1784
01:50:47,559 --> 01:50:50,020
<i>just as long as they aren't also a member.</i>

1785
01:50:50,187 --> 01:50:53,607
<i>It's like a license to steal.
A license to do anything.</i>

1786
01:50:55,776 --> 01:50:57,778
TOMMY: How many years ago
since you were made?

1787
01:50:57,945 --> 01:51:00,697
VINNIE: I'm an old-timer. 30 years ago.
TOMMY: Thirty years?

1788
01:51:00,864 --> 01:51:05,118
Brings back a lot of memories.
Pike's Peak was a pimple then, wasn't it?

1789
01:51:08,413 --> 01:51:11,375
HENRY: <i>As far as Jimmy was concerned,
with Tommy being made...</i>

1790
01:51:11,542 --> 01:51:13,919
<i>it was like we were all being made.</i>

1791
01:51:14,795 --> 01:51:17,339
<i>We would now have
one of our own as a member.</i>

1792
01:51:28,892 --> 01:51:30,102
TOMMY:
Oh, no--

1793
01:51:33,105 --> 01:51:34,985
- Who's this?
- VINNIE [ON PHONE]: <i>This is Vinnie.</i>

1794
01:51:35,107 --> 01:51:37,943
Vinnie. What happened?
Did we get straightened out?

1795
01:51:38,110 --> 01:51:41,113
<i>No, we had a problem.
We tried to do everything we could.</i>

1796
01:51:41,280 --> 01:51:42,322
What do you mean?

1797
01:51:42,489 --> 01:51:46,618
<i>You know what I mean. He's gone,
and we couldn't do nothing about it.</i>

1798
01:51:48,495 --> 01:51:50,372
<i>- That's it.</i>
- What do you mean?

1799
01:51:50,539 --> 01:51:51,915
<i>He's gone.</i>

1800
01:51:53,876 --> 01:51:54,918
<i>That's it.</i>

1801
01:51:59,798 --> 01:52:02,634
I knew it! I can't fucking believe it.

1802
01:52:04,720 --> 01:52:06,722
[CRYING]

1803
01:52:13,020 --> 01:52:15,147
- What happened?
- They fucking whacked him.

1804
01:52:15,314 --> 01:52:16,481
HENRY:
Fuck.

1805
01:52:32,331 --> 01:52:33,999
Are you all right?

1806
01:52:41,048 --> 01:52:43,550
HENRY:
<i>It was revenge for Billy Batts...</i>

1807
01:52:43,717 --> 01:52:45,469
<i>and a lot of other things.</i>

1808
01:52:45,636 --> 01:52:46,678
VINNIE:
And that's that.

1809
01:52:46,845 --> 01:52:49,348
HENRY:
<i>There was nothing we could do about it.</i>

1810
01:52:49,514 --> 01:52:52,142
<i>Batts was a made man
and Tommy wasn't.</i>

1811
01:52:52,726 --> 01:52:54,519
<i>We had to sit still and take it.</i>

1812
01:52:54,686 --> 01:52:58,273
<i>It was among the Italians.
It was real greaseball shit.</i>

1813
01:53:10,911 --> 01:53:12,746
<i>They even shot Tommy in the face...</i>

1814
01:53:12,913 --> 01:53:16,375
<i>so his mother couldn't give him
an open coffin at the funeral.</i>

1815
01:54:03,880 --> 01:54:07,175
HENRY: <i>I was gonna be busy all day.
I had to drop off some guns at Jimmy's...</i>

1816
01:54:07,342 --> 01:54:09,011
<i>to match some silencers he had.</i>

1817
01:54:09,177 --> 01:54:12,264
<i>I had to pick up my brother at the hospital
and drive him home.</i>

1818
01:54:12,431 --> 01:54:14,850
<i>I had to pick up
some new Pittsburgh stuff for Lois...</i>

1819
01:54:15,017 --> 01:54:18,270
<i>to fly down to some customers
I had near Atlanta.</i>

1820
01:54:29,573 --> 01:54:33,035
<i>Right away, I knew he didn't want them,
and I'd be stuck for the money.</i>

1821
01:54:33,201 --> 01:54:36,913
<i>I only bought them because
he wanted them, and now he didn't.</i>

1822
01:54:37,622 --> 01:54:41,126
What good are these? None of them fit.
What's the matter with you?

1823
01:54:41,293 --> 01:54:42,502
I'm not paying for it.

1824
01:54:42,669 --> 01:54:46,381
HENRY: <i>I didn't say a thing. Jimmy was
so pissed off, he didn't even say goodbye.</i>

1825
01:54:46,548 --> 01:54:48,800
Stop the drugs. They're making
your mind into mush!

1826
01:54:48,967 --> 01:54:50,407
- You hear me?
- I'll take them back.

1827
01:55:04,024 --> 01:55:05,984
HENRY:
<i>My Pittsburgh guys always wanted guns.</i>

1828
01:55:06,151 --> 01:55:09,738
<i>Since I would see them in the afternoon
to pick up a delivery...</i>

1829
01:55:09,905 --> 01:55:12,491
<i>I was pretty sure I'd get my money back.</i>

1830
01:55:20,957 --> 01:55:22,334
[TIRES SCREECHING]

1831
01:55:31,510 --> 01:55:32,594
Oh, my God.

1832
01:55:34,346 --> 01:55:38,391
HENRY: <i>When I finally got to the hospital,
Michael's doctor wanted to put me in bed.</i>

1833
01:55:38,558 --> 01:55:40,685
Jesus Christ, what happened to you?

1834
01:55:41,728 --> 01:55:44,106
I almost got into an accident
on the way here.

1835
01:55:44,272 --> 01:55:47,192
<i>And I told him I was partying all night.</i>

1836
01:55:47,359 --> 01:55:49,152
- I'm fine.
- Come on. Get over here.

1837
01:55:49,319 --> 01:55:51,404
- Doc, I'm fine.
- Let me check you out.

1838
01:55:51,905 --> 01:55:53,073
Come on.

1839
01:55:56,118 --> 01:55:58,787
HENRY: <i>He took mercy on me,
gave me 10 milligrams of Valium...</i>

1840
01:55:58,954 --> 01:56:00,038
<i>and sent me home.</i>

1841
01:56:00,747 --> 01:56:04,501
<i>My plan was to drop off my brother
at the house and pick up Karen.</i>

1842
01:56:06,545 --> 01:56:09,756
HENRY: There it is.
You see that helicopter right there?

1843
01:56:09,923 --> 01:56:13,260
Right in front of us, there.
I think it's been following me all morning.

1844
01:56:13,426 --> 01:56:16,179
- Get the fuck out. What are you, nuts?
- I'm telling you.

1845
01:56:16,346 --> 01:56:17,806
I don't know what's going on.

1846
01:56:17,973 --> 01:56:20,851
It's the third time I've seen it.
At the hospital I saw it.

1847
01:56:21,017 --> 01:56:23,395
I had to make some stops.
I've seen it every time.

1848
01:56:23,562 --> 01:56:25,981
I've been all over town
and I've seen it all day.

1849
01:56:32,946 --> 01:56:34,573
HENRY:
<i>I was cooking dinner that night.</i>

1850
01:56:35,699 --> 01:56:39,369
<i>I had to start braising the beef
and veal shanks for the tomato sauce.</i>

1851
01:56:42,038 --> 01:56:45,250
<i>It was Michael's favorite.
I was making ziti with meat gravy...</i>

1852
01:56:45,417 --> 01:56:47,919
<i>and I'm planning to roast some peppers
over the flames...</i>

1853
01:56:48,086 --> 01:56:52,048
<i>put on some string beans with olive oil.
I had some beautiful cutlets...</i>

1854
01:56:52,215 --> 01:56:53,295
<i>that were cut just right...</i>

1855
01:56:53,425 --> 01:56:56,344
<i>that I was going to fry up as an appetizer.</i>

1856
01:56:56,511 --> 01:56:58,597
<i>So I was home for about an hour.</i>

1857
01:56:58,805 --> 01:57:00,765
<i>My plan was to start the dinner early...</i>

1858
01:57:00,932 --> 01:57:03,476
<i>so Karen and I could unload the guns
Jimmy didn't want...</i>

1859
01:57:03,643 --> 01:57:05,061
<i>then get the package for Lois...</i>

1860
01:57:05,228 --> 01:57:07,772
<i>to take to Atlanta for her trip
later that night.</i>

1861
01:57:08,648 --> 01:57:12,444
<i>I kept looking out the window,
and I saw that the helicopter was gone.</i>

1862
01:57:13,069 --> 01:57:16,573
Michael, keep an eye on the sauce.
Stay here with your Uncle Michael.

1863
01:57:17,699 --> 01:57:21,453
<i>So I asked my brother to watch the sauce,
and Karen and I started out.</i>

1864
01:57:24,372 --> 01:57:26,458
Oh, God. I see it.

1865
01:57:26,708 --> 01:57:29,211
- I see it. Look, it's right there.
- Damn!

1866
01:57:30,420 --> 01:57:31,838
- That's it.
- KAREN: There it is.

1867
01:57:32,005 --> 01:57:33,632
We got to get to your mother's.

1868
01:57:34,257 --> 01:57:35,508
See, I told you.

1869
01:57:35,717 --> 01:57:37,093
It's funny.

1870
01:57:37,469 --> 01:57:40,472
- It's not the end of the world.
- We're going to your mother's.

1871
01:58:09,042 --> 01:58:12,712
Go inside, tell your mother not to touch
anything outside the house. Nothing.

1872
01:58:12,879 --> 01:58:15,632
We couldn't go to your mother's house?
You had to come here.

1873
01:58:21,179 --> 01:58:22,847
Let's go shopping.

1874
01:58:25,100 --> 01:58:27,227
I'm not nuts,
it's been following me all morning.

1875
01:58:28,395 --> 01:58:29,521
I'm telling you.

1876
01:58:30,522 --> 01:58:33,775
Fine. Fine. He thinks I'm paranoid!

1877
01:58:34,859 --> 01:58:38,238
I should bring him the helicopter,
then we'll see how paranoid I am.

1878
01:58:40,240 --> 01:58:41,866
Come on, let's go inside.

1879
01:58:46,246 --> 01:58:48,164
- Yeah, it's gone.
- I don't hear anything.

1880
01:58:48,331 --> 01:58:49,571
Let's go back to your mother's.

1881
01:59:03,513 --> 01:59:06,057
- HENRY: They all right?
- Beautiful. They're great.

1882
01:59:06,891 --> 01:59:09,561
Didn't I tell you, you were paranoid?
Didn't I tell him?

1883
01:59:09,728 --> 01:59:11,229
Yeah. I need a hit.

1884
01:59:11,813 --> 01:59:14,816
Want to see helicopters?
Come on, I'll show you helicopters.

1885
01:59:14,983 --> 01:59:17,902
I've seen enough helicopters for one day,
thank you.

1886
01:59:18,903 --> 01:59:23,283
HENRY: <i>I had to get home and get the
package ready for Lois to take on her trip.</i>

1887
01:59:23,450 --> 01:59:26,250
<i>Also, I had to get to Sandy's to give
the package a whack with quinine.</i>

1888
01:59:26,411 --> 01:59:27,495
[PHONE RINGING]

1889
01:59:27,662 --> 01:59:29,914
<i>Plus, I knew Sandy would get on my ass.</i>

1890
01:59:30,081 --> 01:59:33,793
<i>I had the cooking to finish,
and I had to get Lois ready for her trip.</i>

1891
01:59:33,960 --> 01:59:36,504
- It's Sandy. What is this?
- She's a pain in the ass.

1892
01:59:37,213 --> 01:59:38,893
SANDY [ON PHONE]:
<i>When are you coming over?</i>

1893
01:59:39,049 --> 01:59:40,925
- In an hour.
<i>- You staying tonight, right?</i>

1894
01:59:41,092 --> 01:59:43,094
I can't. I got my brother tonight.

1895
01:59:43,428 --> 01:59:47,515
Come on, stop.
We'll talk about it later, okay? Goodbye.

1896
01:59:53,229 --> 01:59:54,522
[RINGS]

1897
01:59:55,148 --> 01:59:57,150
- Hello?
- HENRY [ON PHONE]: <i>It's me. You ready?</i>

1898
01:59:58,318 --> 02:00:00,987
Tell Michael not to let the sauce stick.
Keep stirring it.

1899
02:00:01,571 --> 02:00:05,408
- Henry says don't let the sauce stick.
- I'm stirring it.

1900
02:00:05,575 --> 02:00:07,452
<i>- Listen, you know what to do?</i>
- Yeah, yeah.

1901
02:00:07,619 --> 02:00:09,788
Don't "yeah, yeah" me, Lois.
This is important.

1902
02:00:09,954 --> 02:00:12,415
Make sure you leave the house
when you make the call.

1903
02:00:12,582 --> 02:00:15,794
Understand me?
Call from an outside line. I mean it.

1904
02:00:15,960 --> 02:00:19,798
Jesus, you must think I'm dumb. Why
are you bugging me? I know what to do.

1905
02:00:19,964 --> 02:00:22,258
You little hick, just make sure you do it.

1906
02:00:22,425 --> 02:00:23,468
<i>You can be such a pain.</i>

1907
02:00:23,635 --> 02:00:27,597
<i>- Hey! Just do it!</i>
- Okay.

1908
02:00:28,390 --> 02:00:32,894
Un-fucking-believable. All of them.
Every fucking girl in my life.

1909
02:00:34,270 --> 02:00:36,398
- What did he say?
- Nothing.

1910
02:00:36,564 --> 02:00:38,858
HENRY: <i>What does she do
after she hangs up with me?</i>

1911
02:00:39,025 --> 02:00:42,529
<i>After everything I told her?
After all her "yeah, yeah" bullshit?</i>

1912
02:00:42,695 --> 02:00:45,323
<i>She picks up the phone
and calls from the house.</i>

1913
02:00:45,490 --> 02:00:47,826
<i>If anybody was listening,
they'd know everything.</i>

1914
02:00:47,992 --> 02:00:49,911
<i>They'd know a package
was leaving my house...</i>

1915
02:00:50,078 --> 02:00:53,331
<i>and they'd even have the time and
flight number, thanks to her.</i>

1916
02:00:54,499 --> 02:00:57,168
<i>As soon as I got home, I started cooking.</i>

1917
02:00:57,335 --> 02:00:59,421
<i>I had a few hours until Lois' flight.</i>

1918
02:00:59,587 --> 02:01:01,673
<i>I told my brother to watch the stove.</i>

1919
02:01:01,840 --> 02:01:04,968
<i>All day long the guy's been watching
helicopters and tomato sauce.</i>

1920
02:01:06,428 --> 02:01:11,057
<i>I had to drive over to Sandy's,
mix the stuff, then get back to the gravy.</i>

1921
02:01:22,235 --> 02:01:25,071
Do you think you can come over here,
fuck me, and leave?

1922
02:01:25,447 --> 02:01:27,532
- Come on.
- You got someplace better to go?

1923
02:01:27,699 --> 02:01:30,201
Don't talk like that. Come on.

1924
02:01:30,535 --> 02:01:32,370
- You all right?
- Yeah, sure.

1925
02:01:32,537 --> 02:01:33,580
You believe me?

1926
02:01:34,956 --> 02:01:36,291
Do you believe me?

1927
02:01:36,666 --> 02:01:37,750
Do you believe me?

1928
02:01:40,086 --> 02:01:41,588
- That the last one?
- Yeah.

1929
02:01:49,220 --> 02:01:50,972
[LAUGHS]

1930
02:01:51,431 --> 02:01:53,266
You lying son of a bitch. I hate you!

1931
02:02:00,482 --> 02:02:04,277
Please stop feeding the dog
from the table...

1932
02:02:04,444 --> 02:02:06,738
from the plate on top of it. Stop it.

1933
02:02:06,905 --> 02:02:09,240
- I have to.
- You don't have to.

1934
02:02:14,204 --> 02:02:15,663
I got to go home.

1935
02:02:17,707 --> 02:02:19,626
What do you mean, you got to go home?

1936
02:02:19,792 --> 02:02:21,085
I've been carrying this all day.

1937
02:02:21,252 --> 02:02:23,880
We got to start taping it to your leg.
We got to go soon.

1938
02:02:24,047 --> 02:02:25,965
I got to go home and get my hat.

1939
02:02:26,883 --> 02:02:29,093
Forget your fucking hat.
Are you kidding me?

1940
02:02:29,677 --> 02:02:32,430
So I need a trip to Rockaway
because you want your hat?

1941
02:02:32,597 --> 02:02:36,476
I need it, I got to have it.
It's my lucky hat. I never fly without it.

1942
02:02:36,851 --> 02:02:40,772
Lois, do you understand
what we are involved in here?

1943
02:02:41,231 --> 02:02:44,275
I don't care. I need my hat.
I won't fly without it.

1944
02:02:49,405 --> 02:02:52,992
HENRY: <i>What could I do if she insisted
I drive her home for her goddamn hat?</i>

1945
02:02:53,159 --> 02:02:55,662
<i>I hid the package in the kitchen
and went to take her home.</i>

1946
02:02:55,828 --> 02:02:56,871
A hat?

1947
02:03:06,256 --> 02:03:07,423
What the fuck is this?

1948
02:03:07,840 --> 02:03:10,426
MAN: Police! Freeze! Don't you move,
you motherfucker...

1949
02:03:10,593 --> 02:03:13,596
or I'll blow your brains out.
Shut the car off slowly.

1950
02:03:15,056 --> 02:03:17,433
[SIRENS WAILING NEARBY]

1951
02:03:17,600 --> 02:03:19,769
HENRY:
<i>For a second, I thought I was dead.</i>

1952
02:03:19,936 --> 02:03:22,272
<i>But when I heard all the noise,
I knew they were cops.</i>

1953
02:03:22,438 --> 02:03:23,982
<i>Only cops talk that way.</i>

1954
02:03:24,315 --> 02:03:25,483
COP:
Don't fucking move.

1955
02:03:25,650 --> 02:03:29,153
HENRY: <i>If they had been wiseguys,
I wouldn't have heard a thing.</i>

1956
02:03:30,029 --> 02:03:31,656
<i>I would have been dead.</i>

1957
02:03:32,657 --> 02:03:34,117
Michael, lock the door!

1958
02:03:34,284 --> 02:03:36,160
[BANGING ON DOOR]

1959
02:03:36,327 --> 02:03:38,329
[COPS YELLING]

1960
02:03:58,641 --> 02:04:01,311
COP: Talk to me. When was the last time
you took a collar?

1961
02:04:01,728 --> 02:04:03,354
Fuckhead, I'm talking to you.

1962
02:04:03,521 --> 02:04:07,191
You don't want to say a fucking word,
don't. I don't really give a fuck.

1963
02:04:07,358 --> 02:04:11,404
You'll do 25 years. See how much
of a good guy you'll be then.

1964
02:04:11,571 --> 02:04:13,698
HENRY: <i>All day I thought the guys
in the helicopter...</i>

1965
02:04:13,865 --> 02:04:18,369
<i>were local cops busting my balls over
Lufthansa. They turned out to be narcs.</i>

1966
02:04:18,536 --> 02:04:19,579
Just get the lawyer.

1967
02:04:19,746 --> 02:04:23,333
<i>They'd been on me a month.
Phone taps, surveillance, everything.</i>

1968
02:04:23,499 --> 02:04:26,169
COP:
You know the boys. All the pals are here.

1969
02:04:26,336 --> 02:04:29,255
You don't want to talk to me,
you'll have a problem all night.

1970
02:04:30,006 --> 02:04:33,968
Each one of these counts holds
25-to-life in New York State.

1971
02:04:34,135 --> 02:04:38,723
Twenty-five fucking years, pal.
I'll slap your fucking head inside out.

1972
02:04:39,474 --> 02:04:41,726
What, were you guys grocery shopping?

1973
02:04:43,144 --> 02:04:46,981
Are we going to make a cake?
You going to make a fucking cake?

1974
02:04:47,231 --> 02:04:49,400
You got anything good in there?

1975
02:04:51,110 --> 02:04:52,153
Is it good?

1976
02:04:54,572 --> 02:04:56,199
[COP LAUGHING]

1977
02:04:57,241 --> 02:04:58,826
Bye-bye, dickhead.

1978
02:05:01,954 --> 02:05:03,456
See you in Attica, dick.

1979
02:05:03,998 --> 02:05:07,210
KAREN: I spoke to Jimmy.
He offered to give me some money.

1980
02:05:07,877 --> 02:05:11,047
He just wants to know what's happening.
He just wants to talk to you.

1981
02:05:11,214 --> 02:05:12,590
Fuck Jimmy and his money.

1982
02:05:12,757 --> 02:05:15,968
I got to straighten out everything
with Paulie or I'm dead.

1983
02:05:16,886 --> 02:05:18,513
Then you're better off staying in here.

1984
02:05:18,680 --> 02:05:22,266
They could whack me in here as easy
as outside, maybe even easier.

1985
02:05:22,433 --> 02:05:24,060
They're afraid I'll rat them out.

1986
02:05:24,227 --> 02:05:27,855
People are already walking away from me.
I'm dead in here. You got to get me out.

1987
02:05:28,648 --> 02:05:33,277
HENRY: <i>Karen finally got her mother to put
her house up for my bail and I was out.</i>

1988
02:05:33,444 --> 02:05:37,532
<i>I remember I had this feeling
I would be killed right outside the jail.</i>

1989
02:05:37,949 --> 02:05:41,119
<i>I knew Paulie was still pissed at me,
and he's such a hothead.</i>

1990
02:05:41,285 --> 02:05:43,037
<i>And I was worried about Jimmy.</i>

1991
02:05:43,204 --> 02:05:47,500
<i>See, Jimmy knew if Paulie found out
he was into drug deals with me...</i>

1992
02:05:48,209 --> 02:05:51,254
<i>Paulie would have Jimmy whacked
even before me.</i>

1993
02:05:52,964 --> 02:05:54,590
<i>This is the bad time.</i>

1994
02:05:55,466 --> 02:05:57,719
<i>I didn't feel safe until I got home.</i>

1995
02:05:59,554 --> 02:06:03,474
<i>Now my plan was to stay alive
long enough to sell off the dope...</i>

1996
02:06:03,641 --> 02:06:08,062
<i>the cops never found, then disappear
until I can get things straightened out.</i>

1997
02:06:09,647 --> 02:06:10,690
Fuck!

1998
02:06:10,857 --> 02:06:14,610
- Where's the stuff I left, Karen?
- I flushed it down the toilet.

1999
02:06:16,320 --> 02:06:17,363
You what?

2000
02:06:17,989 --> 02:06:20,491
What was I supposed to do?
They were all over the house.

2001
02:06:20,658 --> 02:06:24,954
That was worth $60,000!
I need that money! That's all we got!

2002
02:06:25,121 --> 02:06:27,582
What was I supposed to do?
They had a search warrant!

2003
02:06:27,749 --> 02:06:32,170
That's all the money we had! I was
depending on that! Why did you do that?

2004
02:06:32,712 --> 02:06:35,506
I had to. They were going to find it!

2005
02:06:35,673 --> 02:06:39,677
- They would have never found it!
- They would have, I swear to you!

2006
02:06:41,095 --> 02:06:42,764
They would've found it!

2007
02:06:42,930 --> 02:06:44,015
[KAREN SCREAMING]

2008
02:06:44,182 --> 02:06:45,600
Why did you do that?

2009
02:06:45,767 --> 02:06:49,353
- They would have found it.
- Why did you do that, Karen?

2010
02:06:50,605 --> 02:06:52,523
Oh, my God!

2011
02:06:53,024 --> 02:06:55,943
- KAREN: I had to do it.
- Oh, my God.

2012
02:06:58,529 --> 02:07:00,531
[BOTH CRYING]

2013
02:07:21,385 --> 02:07:23,513
[CAR HORN HONKS]

2014
02:07:32,063 --> 02:07:34,023
HENRY:
<i>Paulie, I'm really sorry.</i>

2015
02:07:36,692 --> 02:07:39,445
I don't know what else to say.
I know I fucked up.

2016
02:07:39,612 --> 02:07:41,280
Yeah, you fucked up.

2017
02:07:45,034 --> 02:07:46,869
But I'm all right now.

2018
02:07:48,412 --> 02:07:52,792
I can be trusted now. I'm clean.
On my kids, I'm clean.

2019
02:07:52,959 --> 02:07:55,169
You looked in my eyes and lied to me.

2020
02:07:56,462 --> 02:07:58,589
You treated me like a fucking jerk.

2021
02:07:59,215 --> 02:08:00,716
Like I was never nothing to you.

2022
02:08:00,883 --> 02:08:03,553
After what you said,
I couldn't come to you.

2023
02:08:04,887 --> 02:08:07,265
You know, I was ashamed.

2024
02:08:10,268 --> 02:08:12,270
I'm ashamed now.

2025
02:08:15,606 --> 02:08:17,775
But I got nowhere else to go, Paulie.

2026
02:08:20,987 --> 02:08:25,283
You're all I've got.
And I really need your help. I really do.

2027
02:08:31,497 --> 02:08:32,582
Take this.

2028
02:08:47,638 --> 02:08:49,765
And now I've got to turn my back on you.

2029
02:09:00,151 --> 02:09:01,819
HENRY:
<i>$3,200.</i>

2030
02:09:02,403 --> 02:09:06,407
<i>That's what he gave me.
$3,200 for a lifetime.</i>

2031
02:09:07,325 --> 02:09:09,535
<i>It wasn't even enough
to pay for the coffin.</i>

2032
02:09:09,744 --> 02:09:11,829
HENRY: <i>We got to get out.</i>
KAREN: <i>I don't want to run.</i>

2033
02:09:11,996 --> 02:09:16,334
I don't want to. Am I supposed to pick up
and leave everything? Go hiding?

2034
02:09:16,751 --> 02:09:19,253
I don't want to do that.
Is that what you want?

2035
02:09:19,420 --> 02:09:21,589
If we stay around here, we're dead.

2036
02:09:22,340 --> 02:09:24,175
You got it? We're dead.

2037
02:09:24,800 --> 02:09:25,843
They're right.

2038
02:09:26,427 --> 02:09:29,388
You took too much of that stuff.
You're totally paranoid.

2039
02:09:32,975 --> 02:09:34,727
How's he doing? Busting his balls or what?

2040
02:09:34,894 --> 02:09:36,020
He's okay.

2041
02:09:37,188 --> 02:09:38,439
They sobered him up.

2042
02:09:38,940 --> 02:09:40,858
Good. Very good. Glad to hear it.

2043
02:09:45,029 --> 02:09:47,323
You know what kind of questions
they're asking him?

2044
02:09:47,490 --> 02:09:49,075
Jimmy, I don't know.

2045
02:09:50,159 --> 02:09:53,704
I got my mind on so many other things.
I got no money....

2046
02:09:54,246 --> 02:09:56,916
The girls are old enough
to read the newspapers.

2047
02:09:57,083 --> 02:09:59,043
Tell him he's got to call me. Okay?

2048
02:09:59,919 --> 02:10:03,547
As soon as you talk to him,
he's got to call me. It's important.

2049
02:10:03,881 --> 02:10:07,426
He doesn't know I came here to see you.
It's like he's crazy.

2050
02:10:07,593 --> 02:10:10,721
- Take this. It's a couple thousand.
- Thanks, Jimmy.

2051
02:10:10,972 --> 02:10:13,057
Don't worry, everything will be all right.

2052
02:10:13,224 --> 02:10:16,394
I got some beautiful Dior dresses.
You want to have them?

2053
02:10:16,644 --> 02:10:18,521
Pick out a few for yourself.

2054
02:10:19,313 --> 02:10:20,982
- For my mom.
- Yeah, whatever.

2055
02:10:21,399 --> 02:10:24,068
No. It's over here.
In the store on the corner.

2056
02:10:24,235 --> 02:10:26,654
It's swag, so I got it down on the corner.

2057
02:10:32,618 --> 02:10:34,120
Go ahead, sweetheart, I'll see you.

2058
02:10:34,578 --> 02:10:36,288
- Thanks, Jimmy.
- Don't worry.

2059
02:10:36,497 --> 02:10:39,083
- I'll try.
- Don't forget, he's got to call me.

2060
02:10:41,711 --> 02:10:43,921
- Over here?
- Right down there.

2061
02:10:58,936 --> 02:11:00,563
It's over there, on the corner.

2062
02:11:01,272 --> 02:11:02,565
Right there.

2063
02:11:19,957 --> 02:11:22,126
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

2064
02:11:24,628 --> 02:11:26,213
MAN:
Shh, shh, shh.

2065
02:11:36,766 --> 02:11:38,893
No, go ahead. It's right in there.

2066
02:11:39,060 --> 02:11:41,145
KAREN:
No, Jimmy. I'm in a hurry!

2067
02:11:41,479 --> 02:11:44,273
My mom's watching the kids!
I got to get home!

2068
02:11:44,440 --> 02:11:45,983
I'll come back later!

2069
02:11:49,320 --> 02:11:50,821
[TIRES SCREECHING]

2070
02:12:08,422 --> 02:12:10,049
Karen. Karen!

2071
02:12:10,591 --> 02:12:12,093
[KAREN CRYING]

2072
02:12:14,553 --> 02:12:15,805
What happened?

2073
02:12:17,014 --> 02:12:18,474
KAREN:
Nothing.

2074
02:12:18,641 --> 02:12:20,518
- What happened?
- I just got scared.

2075
02:12:24,021 --> 02:12:25,189
Got the keys?

2076
02:12:26,941 --> 02:12:30,569
- What happened, Karen?
- I just got scared. It's okay.

2077
02:12:30,736 --> 02:12:32,363
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

2078
02:12:39,245 --> 02:12:43,833
HENRY: <i>If you're part of a crew, nobody
ever tells you they're going to kill you.</i>

2079
02:12:44,375 --> 02:12:46,127
<i>It doesn't happen that way.</i>

2080
02:12:46,293 --> 02:12:49,713
<i>There aren't any arguments
or curses like in the movies.</i>

2081
02:12:49,880 --> 02:12:53,968
<i>Your murderers come with smiles.
They come as your friends.</i>

2082
02:12:54,135 --> 02:12:56,178
<i>People who cared for you all your life.</i>

2083
02:12:56,345 --> 02:13:00,724
<i>They always seem to come when you're
weakest and most in need of their help.</i>

2084
02:13:01,058 --> 02:13:04,311
<i>So I met Jimmy in a crowded place
we both knew.</i>

2085
02:13:04,687 --> 02:13:08,691
<i>I got there 15 minutes early,
and Jimmy was already there.</i>

2086
02:13:09,108 --> 02:13:13,529
<i>He took the booth near the window
so he could see everyone who drove up.</i>

2087
02:13:13,863 --> 02:13:16,240
<i>He wanted to make sure I wasn't tailed.</i>

2088
02:13:16,657 --> 02:13:19,535
<i>He was jumpy. He hadn't touched a thing.</i>

2089
02:13:20,578 --> 02:13:23,581
<i>On the surface,
everything was supposed to be fine.</i>

2090
02:13:23,747 --> 02:13:26,083
<i>We were supposed to be discussing
my case.</i>

2091
02:13:26,250 --> 02:13:31,213
<i>But I had a feeling Jimmy was trying
to sense if I'd rat on him to save my neck.</i>

2092
02:13:32,882 --> 02:13:36,594
I been telling you your whole life,
don't talk on the phone.

2093
02:13:36,802 --> 02:13:38,596
Now you understand?

2094
02:13:41,265 --> 02:13:44,602
It's going to be okay.
You got a good chance to beat the case.

2095
02:13:47,771 --> 02:13:52,067
You know that kid from the city
we were talking about? You know?

2096
02:13:54,653 --> 02:13:58,657
The kid turned out to be a rat. As soon as
he got pinched, he ratted on everybody.

2097
02:14:01,452 --> 02:14:03,370
I know where he is. He's hiding now.

2098
02:14:05,289 --> 02:14:06,624
Know what I'm saying?

2099
02:14:11,629 --> 02:14:14,798
Would you have a problem going
with Anthony to take care of that?

2100
02:14:15,382 --> 02:14:16,967
Mm-mm.

2101
02:14:17,885 --> 02:14:19,136
No, not at all.

2102
02:14:20,763 --> 02:14:22,348
That way they got nothing.

2103
02:14:31,190 --> 02:14:33,943
HENRY: <i>Jimmy had never asked me
to whack somebody before.</i>

2104
02:14:34,401 --> 02:14:38,072
<i>But now he's asking me to go to Florida
and do a hit with Anthony.</i>

2105
02:14:45,621 --> 02:14:48,958
<i>That's when I knew I would never
have come back from Florida alive.</i>

2106
02:15:03,347 --> 02:15:06,642
Whenever you move me,
I asked once and I'll tell you again...

2107
02:15:06,809 --> 02:15:08,644
I don't want to go any place cold.

2108
02:15:09,645 --> 02:15:11,814
You don't have a choice in that matter.

2109
02:15:12,189 --> 02:15:14,733
Come on. Whoever fucking controls it...

2110
02:15:15,526 --> 02:15:18,195
just no place cold. Do that for me.
I'm trying to--

2111
02:15:18,362 --> 02:15:20,072
He's bronchial, that's why.

2112
02:15:20,239 --> 02:15:22,950
If he's legitimately bronchial,
we'll consider that.

2113
02:15:23,117 --> 02:15:25,202
I'd like to go someplace not cold.

2114
02:15:25,369 --> 02:15:29,081
Can I ask you some questions?
What about my parents?

2115
02:15:30,040 --> 02:15:31,083
What about them?

2116
02:15:31,250 --> 02:15:33,836
Am I going to see them?
Am I going to talk to them?

2117
02:15:35,087 --> 02:15:37,298
Don't I have some kind of contact
with them?

2118
02:15:38,173 --> 02:15:39,216
No.

2119
02:15:40,342 --> 02:15:43,679
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
You mean to tell me that...

2120
02:15:44,054 --> 02:15:48,058
God forbid something happens to my
parents, they get sick, I can't see them?

2121
02:15:48,225 --> 02:15:51,228
Maybe something can be worked out
if they're sick...

2122
02:15:51,729 --> 02:15:53,897
if there's extraordinary circumstances--

2123
02:15:54,064 --> 02:15:56,900
I can't do this. I can't do this, Henry.

2124
02:15:58,027 --> 02:15:59,778
I can't leave my parents.

2125
02:16:01,030 --> 02:16:03,240
Excuse me, Karen, I told you before.

2126
02:16:04,491 --> 02:16:07,494
I'm not going to do this
unless you and the kids come with me.

2127
02:16:09,830 --> 02:16:11,498
I can't do it without you.

2128
02:16:11,915 --> 02:16:16,003
So, you do whatever, but... that's it.

2129
02:16:17,546 --> 02:16:20,007
- You need Henry, not me, right?
- That's right.

2130
02:16:20,424 --> 02:16:22,885
Frankly, I don't care
whether you go or not.

2131
02:16:23,218 --> 02:16:26,597
If it'll make him a better witness,
I'd like you to be with him.

2132
02:16:26,764 --> 02:16:28,349
They want Henry, not me.

2133
02:16:28,515 --> 02:16:31,602
Henry'll be in the protection program.
They can't get to him.

2134
02:16:32,519 --> 02:16:35,773
They can only get to him
by getting to you or your kids.

2135
02:16:35,939 --> 02:16:38,525
If he goes into the program,
you're in danger--

2136
02:16:38,692 --> 02:16:41,070
- I don't know anything.
- Don't give me...

2137
02:16:41,236 --> 02:16:42,738
the babe-in-the-woods routine.

2138
02:16:42,905 --> 02:16:47,284
I've listened to those wiretaps,
and I've heard you talk about cocaine.

2139
02:16:47,451 --> 02:16:50,788
<i>Conversation after conversation
you talked to Henry on the phone.</i>

2140
02:16:56,001 --> 02:16:58,087
It doesn't matter.
Whether he goes to jail...

2141
02:16:58,253 --> 02:17:01,548
or stays on the streets and beats the case,
he's a dead man.

2142
02:17:02,299 --> 02:17:04,009
He knows it and you know it.

2143
02:17:05,636 --> 02:17:07,346
What about the kids and school?

2144
02:17:07,513 --> 02:17:09,807
KAREN: <i>Will they get left back?
I mean, what goes on?</i>

2145
02:17:10,140 --> 02:17:12,559
TUDDY:
Go to Wall Street and get real crooks.

2146
02:17:12,726 --> 02:17:15,187
Whoever sold you those suits
had a sense of humor.

2147
02:17:15,354 --> 02:17:18,440
What it comes down to is
we're your only salvation.

2148
02:17:19,274 --> 02:17:22,694
We'll save your life and his life,
and we'll keep you out of jail.

2149
02:17:26,949 --> 02:17:29,576
<i>This morning you told the jury
about your background.</i>

2150
02:17:29,743 --> 02:17:31,578
HENRY:
<i>It was easy for us to disappear.</i>

2151
02:17:32,121 --> 02:17:34,248
<i>My house
was in my mother-in-law's name.</i>

2152
02:17:34,415 --> 02:17:36,375
<i>My cars were registered to my wife.</i>

2153
02:17:36,542 --> 02:17:40,003
<i>My Social Security cards
and driver's licenses were phonies.</i>

2154
02:17:40,170 --> 02:17:42,506
<i>I never voted or paid taxes.</i>

2155
02:17:43,090 --> 02:17:47,553
<i>My birth certificate and arrest sheet was
all you'd ever have to know I was alive.</i>

2156
02:17:47,719 --> 02:17:49,638
ATTORNEY:
Do you see him here in this courtroom?

2157
02:17:49,805 --> 02:17:50,848
Yes.

2158
02:17:51,014 --> 02:17:53,100
ATTORNEY:
Will you please point him out for the jury?

2159
02:17:55,686 --> 02:18:00,315
Let the record reflect that Mr. Hill
identified the defendant, James Conway.

2160
02:18:01,442 --> 02:18:04,528
Do you also know a man
named Paul Cicero?

2161
02:18:04,862 --> 02:18:06,864
- Do you see him in the courtroom?
- Yes.

2162
02:18:07,448 --> 02:18:09,366
ATTORNEY:
Can you point him out for the jury?

2163
02:18:11,326 --> 02:18:15,414
Let the record reflect that Mr. Hill
identified the defendant, Paul Cicero.

2164
02:18:16,748 --> 02:18:18,459
Your Honor, I have a document....

2165
02:18:18,625 --> 02:18:21,044
HENRY:
<i>The hardest thing was leaving the life.</i>

2166
02:18:21,879 --> 02:18:23,338
<i>I still love the life.</i>

2167
02:18:23,714 --> 02:18:25,632
<i>We were treated like movie stars
with muscle.</i>

2168
02:18:25,799 --> 02:18:28,051
<i>We had it all, just for the asking.</i>

2169
02:18:28,218 --> 02:18:31,555
<i>Our wives, mothers, kids,
everybody rode along.</i>

2170
02:18:31,889 --> 02:18:35,058
<i>I had paper bags filled with jewelry
stashed in the kitchen.</i>

2171
02:18:35,225 --> 02:18:37,478
<i>I had a sugar bowl full of coke
next to the bed.</i>

2172
02:18:37,644 --> 02:18:41,440
People call them rats because rats do
anything to survive. Isn't that right?

2173
02:18:41,607 --> 02:18:43,650
ATTORNEY: Objection!
JUDGE: Objection sustained.

2174
02:18:43,817 --> 02:18:47,404
- I know nothing about being a rat.
- You know everything about it.

2175
02:18:47,738 --> 02:18:49,591
ATTORNEY: Objection, Your Honor.
In view of the violence....

2176
02:18:49,615 --> 02:18:51,742
HENRY:
<i>Anything I wanted was a phone call away.</i>

2177
02:18:51,909 --> 02:18:55,329
<i>Free cars. Keys to a dozen hideout flats
all over the city.</i>

2178
02:18:55,496 --> 02:18:57,998
<i>I'd bet $20,000, $30,000
over a weekend...</i>

2179
02:18:58,165 --> 02:19:02,211
<i>then blow the winnings in a week
or go to the sharks to pay the bookies.</i>

2180
02:19:02,377 --> 02:19:03,712
It didn't matter.

2181
02:19:04,254 --> 02:19:09,134
It didn't mean anything. When I was broke
I would go out and rob some more.

2182
02:19:09,551 --> 02:19:10,928
We ran everything.

2183
02:19:11,470 --> 02:19:15,766
We paid off cops. We paid off lawyers.
We paid off judges.

2184
02:19:16,016 --> 02:19:19,436
Everybody had their hands out.
Everything was for the taking.

2185
02:19:21,563 --> 02:19:23,065
And now it's all over.

2186
02:19:23,982 --> 02:19:25,442
<i>That's the hardest part.</i>

2187
02:19:26,443 --> 02:19:28,070
<i>Today everything is different.</i>

2188
02:19:28,237 --> 02:19:32,407
<i>There's no action.
I have to wait around like everyone else.</i>

2189
02:19:32,783 --> 02:19:34,576
<i>Can't even get decent food.</i>

2190
02:19:35,327 --> 02:19:38,455
<i>After I got here I ordered spaghetti
with marinara sauce...</i>

2191
02:19:38,622 --> 02:19:40,457
<i>and I got egg noodles and ketchup.</i>

2192
02:19:41,291 --> 02:19:42,793
<i>I'm an average nobody.</i>

2193
02:19:44,169 --> 02:19:46,964
<i>I get to live the rest of my life
like a schnook.</i>

2194
02:25:11,288 --> 02:25:13,290
[English - US - SDH]

